'''periapsis''' (''plural'' '''periapsides''')

#(''astronomy'') The [[point]] of a [[body]]'s [[elliptical]] [[orbit]] about the [[system]]'s [[centre]] of [[mass]] where the [[distance]] between the body and the centre of mass is at its [[minimum]]. In the case of other [[celestial]] bodies, specialised terms are used. See [[w:en:Apsis|Apsis (Wikipedia)]] for details.

